        </correctfeedback>
        <partiallycorrectfeedback format="html">
            <text></text>
        </partiallycorrectfeedback>
        <incorrectfeedback format="html">
            <text></text>
        </incorrectfeedback>
        <answer fraction="0" format="html">
            <text>
                <![CDATA[<p><span style="color: #000000;">Primer molecules that are <a title="Hybridization probe" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hybridization_probe"><span style="color: #000000;">hybridized</span></a> to each other because of strings of <a title="Complementarity (molecular biology)" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Complementarity_(molecular_biology)"><span style="color: #000000;">complementary</span></a> <a title="Nucleotide" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nucleotide"><span style="color: #000000;">bases</span></a> in the primers.</span></p>]]></text>
            <feedback format="html">
                <text></text>
            </feedback>
        </answer>
        <answer fraction="0" format="html">
            <text><![CDATA[<p>Primer dimers are smaller than PCR products.</p>]]></text>
            <feedback format="html">
                <text></text>
            </feedback>
        </answer>
        <answer fraction="100" format="html">
            <text><![CDATA[<p>They tend to run very slow and may be a bit fuzzy at the top of the gel.</p>]]></text>
            <feedback format="html">
                <text></text>
            </feedback>
        </answer>
        <answer fraction="0" format="html">
            <text>
                <![CDATA[<p><span style="color: #000000;">One approach to prevent PDs consists of physical-chemical optimization of the PCR system, i.e., changing the concentrations of primers, <a title="Magnesium chloride" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Magnesium_chloride"><span style="color: #000000;">magnesium chloride</span></a>, <a title="Nucleotides" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nucleotides"><span style="color: #000000;">nucleotides</span></a>, <a title="Ionic strength" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ionic_strength"><span style="color: #000000;">ionic strength</span></a> and temperature of the reaction.</span></p>]]></text>
            <feedback format="html">
                <text></text>
            </feedback>
        </answer>
        <answer fraction="0" format="html">
            <text><![CDATA[<p>All of the following.</p>]]></text>
            <feedback format="html">
                <text></text>
            </feedback>
        </answer>
    </question>

